{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MapLibre Native iOS provides a set of built-in gesture recognizers. You can customize or supplement these gestures according to your use case. You see what gesture recognizers are on your "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" by accessing the "},{"code":"gestureRecognizers","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property on your map."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Configuring-user-interaction","text":"Configuring user interaction"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Several properties on an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" provide ways to enable or disable a set of gesture recognizers. Boolean values are set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" by default."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/zoomEnabled","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" - Allows the user to zoom in or out by pinching two fingers, double-tapping, tapping with two fingers, or double-tapping then dragging vertically. Accepts Boolean values.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/scrollEnabled","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" - Allows the user to scroll by dragging or swiping one finger. Accepts Boolean values."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/rotateEnabled","isActive":true